---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service - The Realm of Patterns" description="Terms and conditions for using The Realm of Patterns services.">
  <div class="legal-page">
    <div class="page-container">
      <header class="page-header">
        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="effective-date">Effective Date: February 4, 2026</p>
      </header>

      <div class="legal-content">
        <section>
          <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p>
            By accessing or using The Realm of Patterns ("Service"), you agree to be bound by these
            Terms of Service. If you do not agree, please do not use the Service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
          <p>
            The Realm of Patterns provides personalized energy readings and pattern analysis
            based on astronomical data. The Service includes:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Daily check-ins and energy readings</li>
            <li>Daily forecasts and optimal timing recommendations</li>
            <li>Pattern tracking over time</li>
            <li>Team features for group alignment analysis</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>3. Accounts</h2>
          <h3>3.1 Account Creation</h3>
          <p>
            Some features require an account. You must provide accurate information and keep your
            account credentials secure. You are responsible for all activity under your account.
          </p>

          <h3>3.2 Account Termination</h3>
          <p>
            We may suspend or terminate accounts that violate these Terms. You may delete your
            account at any time through your account settings.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>4. Subscriptions and Payments</h2>
          <h3>4.1 Pricing</h3>
          <p>
            Paid features require a subscription. Current pricing is displayed on our subscribe page.
            Prices may change with 30 days notice.
          </p>

          <h3>4.2 Billing</h3>
          <p>
            Subscriptions auto-renew unless cancelled. You will be billed on the same date each month/year.
            Payments are processed securely through Stripe.
          </p>

          <h3>4.3 Refunds</h3>
          <p>
            We offer a 7-day money-back guarantee for Pro and 14 days for Team subscriptions.
            After the trial period, refunds are at our discretion.
          </p>

          <h3>4.4 Cancellation</h3>
          <p>
            Cancel anytime from your account dashboard. You retain access until the end of your billing period.
            No partial refunds for unused time.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>5. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p>You agree not to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Use the Service for any unlawful purpose</li>
            <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any part of the Service</li>
            <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Service</li>
            <li>Scrape, harvest, or collect user data without permission</li>
            <li>Share account credentials with others (except authorized Circle members)</li>
            <li>Resell or redistribute the Service without authorization</li>
            <li>Use the Service to harm, harass, or discriminate against others</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>6. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>
            The Service, including the analytical framework, designs, code, and content, is owned by
            The Realm of Patterns. You may not copy, modify, or distribute our intellectual property
            without permission.
          </p>
          <p>
            You retain ownership of your personal data and check-in responses. By using the Service,
            you grant us a license to use this data to provide and improve the Service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>7. Disclaimers</h2>
          <h3>7.1 Not Professional Advice</h3>
          <p>
            The Service provides pattern insights for personal reflection and entertainment.
            It is NOT a substitute for professional medical, psychological, financial, or legal advice.
            Always consult qualified professionals for important decisions.
          </p>

          <h3>7.2 No Guarantees</h3>
          <p>
            We make no guarantees about the accuracy of predictions or readings. Cosmic patterns
            are interpretive frameworks, not deterministic prophecies. Results vary by individual.
          </p>

          <h3>7.3 Service Availability</h3>
          <p>
            We strive for high availability but cannot guarantee uninterrupted service. We may
            modify or discontinue features with reasonable notice.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, The Realm of Patterns shall not be liable for:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages</li>
            <li>Loss of profits, data, or goodwill</li>
            <li>Decisions made based on readings or recommendations</li>
            <li>Actions of third parties or other users</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Our total liability shall not exceed the amount you paid us in the 12 months preceding the claim.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>9. Indemnification</h2>
          <p>
            You agree to indemnify and hold harmless The Realm of Patterns from any claims, damages,
            or expenses arising from your use of the Service or violation of these Terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>10. Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p>
            The Service may integrate with third parties (Stripe, social login providers, etc.).
            Your use of those services is subject to their terms. We are not responsible for
            third-party services.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>11. Changes to Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these Terms periodically. Material changes will be communicated via email
            or prominent notice. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>12. Governing Law</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms are governed by the laws of the jurisdiction where The Realm of Patterns
            is incorporated, without regard to conflict of law principles.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>13. Dispute Resolution</h2>
          <p>
            Disputes shall be resolved through good-faith negotiation. If unresolved, disputes
            will be submitted to binding arbitration, except where prohibited by law.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>14. Severability</h2>
          <p>
            If any provision is found unenforceable, the remaining provisions continue in effect.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>15. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            For questions about these Terms, contact us at:
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Email:</strong> legal@therealmofpatterns.com
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    --gold: #d4a854;
    --dark: #0a0908;
    --dark-surface: #141210;
    --text: #f0e8d8;
    --text-muted: rgba(240, 232, 216, 0.6);

    font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif;
    background: var(--dark);
    color: var(--text);
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 6rem 2rem 4rem;
  }

  .page-container {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .page-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(212, 168, 84, 0.2);
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif;
  }

  .effective-date {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .legal-content section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .legal-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-content h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-content p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-content ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-content li {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-content li strong {
    color: var(--text);
  }
</style>
